<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 2:16PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southeastern Surry, southwestern Stokes, southeastern Wilkes and
Yadkin Counties through 245 PM EDT...
At 216 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Buck Shoals, or 9 miles south of Jonesville, moving northeast at 30
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Elkin...
Fairview...
Yadkinville...
Jonesville...
Pilot Mountain...
Boonville...
and East Bend.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
